The attack happened last week and the 27-year old suspect was apprehended in Du Noon on Monday morning. CAPE TOWN - Police have arrested a mother for allegedly stabbing her two-year-old son in Khayelitsha.The attack happened last week and the 27-year old suspect was apprehended in Du Noon on Monday morning.The toddler is reportedly in a stable condition in hospital.The police s Frederick van Wyk said: She is expected to make appearance in the Khayelitsha Magistrates Court tomorrow on a charge of attempted murder. The incident occurred at their residence last Monday and the suspect fled thereafter. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)